{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"28701ced-0d71-4def-a6be-bcab615f9605","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs` but depends on it.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_EGnRQfhR7JQ6E7LpgRzpYm","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-4378291988874583aa47947318e9655b/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-4378291988874583aa47947318e9655b/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"2cbfc451-d2fa-404f-9e44-d85328532311","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first) - depends on `Domain.fs` (opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second) - defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third) - depends on both\n\nThe problem is that `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` uses types from `Domain.fs`. In F#, a file can only use things defined in files listed above it.\n\n\nSo I need to reorder them: `Domain.fs` first to define the types, then `Services.fs` which depends on it, and finally `Program.fs` which uses both.","outputTokens":495,"requestId":"DBCB:32F6A4:158C129:181D592:69FD3385"},"id":"da9fc3d5-07de-4faf-b2c9-21f1c432a43e","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:51:25.904Z","parentId":"3ca600a0-52d9-4623-9dfb-87caf672764c"}
